# Testing Standards — {Agent Name}

## Mandatory test categories

Per `design/06-templates.md` and enforced by `doc_lint`:

- **Functional** — happy-path coverage for every FR
- **Negative** — error-path coverage

These two are always required. The following are optional per `project.config.yaml unitTestPolicy.*`:

- **Security** — privilege denial, FLS / OLS / RLS scenarios
- **Multilingual** — labels, RTL, locale-specific formatting (when `multilingual.*` is true)
- **Performance** — load / response time targets per `02-nfr.md`
- **Accessibility** — WCAG checks (UI artefacts only)
- **E2E** — cross-component / cross-system journeys
- **Regression** — against a stable baseline

## Per-artifact-type testing harness

If the platform has a specific testing framework (e.g., FakeXrmEasy for CE plugins, PCF test harness, Power Fx tests, SysTest for F&O, FakePxe), document setup + conventions here.

## Test plan layout

Per `design/06-templates.md` § Test plan, `/test-plan` produces a folder, not a single file:

```
test-plan/
├── index.md                    # strategy, suite list, coverage summary, traceability
├── suites/
│   └── NN-{slug}.md            # one per suite, all TCs inline
├── coverage-report.md          # AUTO-GENERATED by doc_lint
└── traceability.yaml           # machine-readable for ALM sync
```

## Test case ID convention

Per-suite numbering: `S{NN}-TC-{NNN}` (e.g., `S01-TC-001`). Suite prefix avoids ripple renumbering when suites are added.

## Coverage gates

`doc_lint` produces `coverage-report.md` on every `/test-plan` run. Functional + Negative coverage gaps **fail the write** unless `/test-plan --waive-coverage` is used (logged loudly, surfaces in `/status`).
